  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Team management within carnivals involves organizing your club's players into carnival teams, managing player assignments, and coordinating team logistics after your club has been approved to participate.</p>

  <h3>Team Management Workflow</h3>

  <h4>Post-Registration Team Building</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Registration Approval</strong> — Wait for carnival organizers to approve your registration</li>
    <li><strong>Access Team Management</strong> — Navigate to your approved carnival registration</li>
    <li><strong>Select Players</strong> — Choose players from your club roster to assign to the team</li>
    <li><strong>Manage Assignments</strong> — Add, remove, or change player assignments as needed</li>
    <li><strong>Team Coordination</strong> — Communicate with your team and coordinate logistics</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Team Management Areas</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Player Selection</strong> — Choose which players will participate in the carnival</li>
    <li><strong>Team Roster</strong> — View and manage your current team composition</li>
    <li><strong>Player Information</strong> — Access player details, medical info, and emergency contacts</li>
    <li><strong>Team Communication</strong> — Coordinate with team members and carnival organizers</li>
    <li><strong>Logistics Planning</strong> — Handle travel, accommodation, and equipment needs</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Building Your Carnival Team</h3>

  <h4>Accessing Team Management</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Find Your Registration</strong> — Go to your dashboard and find the registered carnival</li>
    <li><strong>Open Team Management</strong> — Click on the carnival to access team management options</li>
    <li><strong>Navigate to Players</strong> — Find the "Players" or "Team" section for your registration</li>
    <li><strong>Add Team Members</strong> — Use the "Add Players" option to build your roster</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Player Selection Process</h4>

  <h5>Available Players</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Club Roster</strong> — All active players from your club are available for selection</li>
    <li><strong>Player Status</strong> — Only active players can be assigned to carnival teams</li>
    <li><strong>Previous Assignments</strong> — Players already assigned to this carnival won't appear in available list</li>
    <li><strong>Player Information</strong> — View player details, medical info, and contact information</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Selecting Multiple Players</h5>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Browse Available Players</strong> — View the list of players available for selection</li>
    <li><strong>Select Players</strong> — Check the boxes next to players you want to add</li>
    <li><strong>Bulk Selection</strong> — Use "Select All" to select all available players if desired</li>
    <li><strong>Review Selections</strong> — Check that your selections are correct</li>
    <li><strong>Add to Team</strong> — Click "Add Players" to assign selected players to your team</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Team Size Considerations</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Carnival Limits</strong> — Be aware of any team size limits set by organizers</li>
    <li><strong>Squad Depth</strong> — Consider having backup players for injuries or unavailability</li>
    <li><strong>Player Fitness</strong> — Ensure selected players are fit and ready to participate</li>
    <li><strong>Team Balance</strong> — Consider player positions and team composition</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Managing Your Team Roster</h3>

  <h4>Viewing Team Composition</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Current Roster</strong> — See all players currently assigned to your carnival team</li>
    <li><strong>Player Details</strong> — Access individual player information and contact details</li>
    <li><strong>Assignment Status</strong> — Track which players have confirmed their participation</li>
    <li><strong>Team Statistics</strong> — View team size, player demographics, and other metrics</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Player Management Actions</h4>

  <h5>Adding Players</h5>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Access Add Players</strong> — Navigate to the add players section</li>
    <li><strong>Select from Available</strong> — Choose players from your club's available roster</li>
    <li><strong>Multiple Selection</strong> — Select multiple players at once when possible</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm Addition</strong> — Add selected players to your carnival team</li>
  </ol>

  <h5>Removing Players</h5>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Identify Player</strong> — Find the player you want to remove from the team roster</li>
    <li><strong>Access Options</strong> — Look for remove or delete options next to the player</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm Removal</strong> — Confirm that you want to remove the player</li>
    <li><strong>Update Team</strong> — The player will be removed and become available for selection again</li>
  </ol>

  <h5>Viewing Player Information</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Contact Details</strong> — Access player phone numbers and email addresses</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Information</strong> — Review medical conditions, allergies, and emergency contacts</li>
    <li><strong>Player Notes</strong> — View additional notes about the player</li>
    <li><strong>Participation History</strong> — See previous carnival participation</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Team Communication and Coordination</h3>

  <h4>Player Communication</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Contact Information</strong> — Access all team members' contact details</li>
    <li><strong>Group Communication</strong> — Send messages to your entire carnival team</li>
    <li><strong>Individual Updates</strong> — Contact specific players when needed</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Contacts</strong> — Access emergency contact information for all players</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Carnival Updates</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Organizer Communications</strong> — Receive updates from carnival organizers</li>
    <li><strong>Schedule Changes</strong> — Stay informed about any changes to carnival schedule</li>
    <li><strong>Venue Information</strong> — Get updates about venues, facilities, and logistics</li>
    <li><strong>Team Requirements</strong> — Receive information about equipment, uniforms, or other requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Team Logistics Planning</h3>

  <h4>Pre-Carnival Preparation</h4>

  <h5>Travel and Accommodation</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Team Travel</strong> — Coordinate transportation arrangements for the team</li>
    <li><strong>Accommodation</strong> — Arrange accommodation if required by the carnival</li>
    <li><strong>Meeting Points</strong> — Establish team meeting locations and times</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Plans</strong> — Develop emergency communication and meeting plans</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Equipment and Uniforms</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Team Uniforms</strong> — Ensure all players have appropriate uniforms</li>
    <li><strong>Equipment Check</strong> — Verify all necessary rugby league equipment is available</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Supplies</strong> — Ensure medical kits and supplies are prepared</li>
    <li><strong>Personal Equipment</strong> — Remind players to bring personal items (mouthguards, boots, etc.)</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Medical and Safety Preparation</h4>

  <h5>Player Health Information</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Medical Reviews</strong> — Review all players' medical information before the carnival</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Contacts</strong> — Verify emergency contact details are current</li>
    <li><strong>Allergies and Conditions</strong> — Note any allergies, medical conditions, or medications</li>
    <li><strong>Fitness Status</strong> — Ensure players are medically fit to participate</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Emergency Procedures</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Emergency Contacts</strong> — Have emergency contact information readily available</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Facilities</strong> — Know the location of medical facilities at the carnival venue</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Plans</strong> — Develop team emergency response procedures</li>
    <li><strong>Communication Plans</strong> — Establish how the team will communicate during emergencies</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Team Performance and Strategy</h3>

  <h4>Team Composition</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Player Positions</strong> — Consider player positions and team balance</li>
    <li><strong>Experience Levels</strong> — Mix experienced and newer players appropriately</li>
    <li><strong>Team Spirit</strong> — Foster team camaraderie and sportsmanship</li>
    <li><strong>Player Availability</strong> — Confirm all selected players can attend all carnival sessions</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Pre-Carnival Meetings</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Team Meetings</strong> — Hold team meetings to discuss strategy and expectations</li>
    <li><strong>Player Introductions</strong> — Ensure team members know each other</li>
    <li><strong>Rules Review</strong> — Review carnival rules and format</li>
    <li><strong>Goals Setting</strong> — Discuss team goals and individual player objectives</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Handling Team Changes</h3>

  <h4>Player Unavailability</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Receive Notification</strong> — Be informed when a player cannot attend</li>
    <li><strong>Assess Impact</strong> — Evaluate the impact on team composition</li>
    <li><strong>Find Replacement</strong> — Identify available replacement players if needed</li>
    <li><strong>Update Team</strong> — Add replacement player and remove unavailable player</li>
    <li><strong>Communicate Changes</strong> — Inform team members and organizers about changes</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Team Size Adjustments</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Carnival Requirements</strong> — Adjust team size to meet carnival requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Player Availability</strong> — Modify team based on actual player availability</li>
    <li><strong>Strategic Decisions</strong> — Make tactical adjustments based on team strengths</li>
    <li><strong>Organizer Communication</strong> — Keep organizers informed about team changes</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Post-Carnival Activities</h3>

  <h4>Team Wrap-up</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Team Feedback</strong> — Gather feedback from players about the carnival experience</li>
    <li><strong>Performance Review</strong> — Review team and individual player performance</li>
    <li><strong>Photo and Memories</strong> — Collect team photos and memorable moments</li>
    <li><strong>Thank You Notes</strong> — Send thanks to organizers and host clubs</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Record Keeping</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Participation Records</strong> — Maintain records of player participation</li>
    <li><strong>Team Statistics</strong> — Track team performance and individual achievements</li>
    <li><strong>Lessons Learned</strong> — Document what worked well and areas for improvement</li>
    <li><strong>Future Planning</strong> — Use experience to improve future carnival participation</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Best Practices for Team Management</h3>

  <h4>Communication</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Regular Updates</strong> — Keep team members informed about carnival developments</li>
    <li><strong>Clear Expectations</strong> — Set clear expectations for player participation and behavior</li>
    <li><strong>Open Dialogue</strong> — Encourage players to communicate concerns or issues</li>
    <li><strong>Timely Responses</strong> — Respond promptly to player inquiries and organizer communications</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Organization</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Player Information</strong> — Maintain accurate and up-to-date player information</li>
    <li><strong>Team Documentation</strong> — Keep records of team decisions and communications</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Preparedness</strong> — Ensure all emergency information is readily available</li>
    <li><strong>Logistics Planning</strong> — Plan thoroughly for travel, accommodation, and equipment needs</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Player Welfare</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Medical Awareness</strong> — Be aware of player medical conditions and needs</li>
    <li><strong>Inclusive Environment</strong> — Foster an inclusive and supportive team environment</li>
    <li><strong>Work-Life Balance</strong> — Respect players' work and personal commitments</li>
    <li><strong>Player Development</strong> — Support player development and skill improvement</li>
  </ul>

